---
description: Ban inline err-handling in if init statements in Go
globs: **/*.go
alwaysApply: false
---

# Go: no inline err handling in `if`

Never write error handling using an `if` init statement (with `;`) such as:

```go
// ❌ BAD
if v, err := strconv.Atoi(s); err == nil {
    limit = v
}

// ❌ BAD
if err := repo.Update(ctx, u); err != nil {
    return err
}
```

Always split into separate assignment + `if err != nil` check:

```go
// ✅ GOOD
v, err := strconv.Atoi(s)
if err == nil {
    limit = v
}

// ✅ GOOD
err = repo.Update(ctx, u)
if err != nil {
    return err
}
```

